CHARTERS OF THE FRIARS PREACHERS OF AYR. 91

ABSTRAOT.

Notarial copy of Brief by Pope Leo the Tenth, to the master general and friars of the Predieant order, granting to them, on the request of Nicolas,

bishop of Alba, cardinal protector of the said order, similar privileges to those enjoyed by the Friars Minors in regard to the observance of certain feast days in towns or places under eeclesiastical interdict ; so that on the feasts of Sts· Dominic, Peter Martyr, Thomas Aquinas, and Vincent, and St. Catherine of Siena, when they should occur in such towns or places, it should be lawful to celebrate divine service in the churches of the convents of the Friars Preachers, the bells being rung and the doors opened, but excluding those who were personally interdicted or excommunicated. Given at Rome, at St Peter'S‚ under the ring of the F isherman, 23d J uly 1518.

58. Sasine in favour qf the Friars Preachers, qf the Walkmill belonyiny

to Adam Wallace qf Newtoun, Zyiny in the Borowfield qf Ayr. -[29th February 1524.]

In Dei nomine Amen: Per hoc presens publicum instrumentum cunctis pateat evidenter et sit notum quod anno incarnacionis Dominice millesimo quingentesimo vicesimo quarto die vero mensis Februarij ultimo indiccione decima tercia pontificatus sanctissimi in Christo patris ac domini nostri domini Clementis divina providencia pape septimi anno secundo in mei notarii publici et testium subscriptorum preseneiis personaliter constitutus Adam Wallace de Newtoun aldermannus de Aire pro tempore non vi aut metu ductus nee errore lapsus seu dolo circumventus sed sua mera pura libera et spontanea voluntate ac utilitateque sua prius undique visa et pensata totum et integrum suum molendinum fullonatorium videlicet ly Walkmyll cum pertinenciis quoad feodum eiusdem jacens infra territorium dicti burgi in ly Borowfeild eiusdem Kingis Kyle et infra vicecomitatum de Aire inter terras de Holmyshill ab una et aquam de Aire ab altera parti- bus in manibus providi viri Ricardi Reid unius ballivorum dicti burgi de Aire pro tempore unacum quadam pecia terre dicto molendino spectante et pertinente et piscaria salmonum de croeis in ly myldam eiusdem per fustis et baculi tradicionem ut moris est sursum reddidit pureque et simpliciter a se et heredibus suis pro imperpetuo resignavit et hoc in favorem Fratrum
